Description: Fragment of neck of a pottery transport amphora. Clay coarse, micaceous, red-brown; small mica; grey core. Circular floral? stamp, deeply stamped, but poorly impressed.
Production place: Made in: Lower Egypt, Nile Delta?
Curator's comments: Not clearly trimmed, but seemingly local Delta production.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1315)
